Title: Relapsing Clostridium difficile enterocolitis cured by rectal infusion of normal faeces.
Abstract: Repeated recurrence of Clostridium difficile-associated enterocolitis is uncommon but troublesome for the afflicted patient. The patient described here received vancomycin treatment several times but always had a relapse of C. Difficile enterocolitis 2-3 weeks after discontinuation of treatment. She did not form serum antibodies to C. Difficile cytotoxin (toxin B). Rectal infusion of enemas prepared from fresh faeces resulted in final cure.
